Both the recent specimens were collect- ed in limestone caves. Yathay-Pyan Cave, which is situated at 50 m above sea level has several large chambers and a complex roof system. It is surrounded by paddy fields and secondary forest. Hintha Cave is at an altitude of
520 m .
It is near a stream and a waterfall. The type locality of P. pa- terculus is Mount Popa, which is a 1500 m high extinct volcano. The summit is grassy. At the time of capture, the upper slopes were covered in temperate evergreen forest and cultivated gardens and the lower slopes with dry decidous forest mixed with bam- boo. The surrounding area is dry, open country (
Wroughton, 1915 a
). At Kyouk Myoung, it was found in thick scrub (
Wroughton, 1915 a
). It is also known from the Shan Plateau having been collected from Pyaunggaung at an altitude of 860 m (
Wroughton, 1916 a
).

